# Phase 3.2 — Self-hosted Sentry telemetry.
#
# Anonymous crash / perf reports flow back to us for product-side decisions.
# Hosters opt-in by setting `sv_alfaTelemetry true` in their server.cfg.
#
# Target files:
#   PATCH: code/client/launcher/CitiLaunch.cpp     — client Sentry init
#   PATCH: code/server/launcher/Launcher.cpp       — server Sentry init
#   NEW:   code/components/citizen-common/src/Telemetry.cpp
#
# === What we collect (opt-in only) ===
#
# Client:
#   - Crashes (minidump + stack trace; no game-state data)
#   - FPS histograms (anonymous; helps us tune perf)
#   - Network metrics: RTT, packet loss, hitch rate
#   - Build version + OS
#
# Server:
#   - Crashes
#   - tick-rate actual vs target
#   - resource start/stop timings
#   - hitch warnings ("server thread hitch warning" log)
#   - peak player count per hour
#
# === What we DO NOT collect ===
#
# - Player identifiers (no usernames, no IPs, no HWIDs)
# - Game state (positions, chat, vehicles)
# - Server admin actions
# - Voice
# - Hoster identity (only an anonymized random ID per server)
#
# === Infrastructure ===
#
# Self-hosted Sentry via docker-compose on our existing VPS:
#   infra/sentry/docker-compose.yml
# Public DSN exposed at: https://sentry.alfamp.gg/<project>
#
# Storage: 30 days retention, then auto-delete (GDPR compliant).
#
# === Convars ===
#
#   sv_alfaTelemetry      true|false     default FALSE (opt-in)
#   sv_alfaTelemetryUrl   url            default our public DSN
#
# Hoster sees "Telemetry: ON — helping Alfa MP improve" banner in admin
# console if enabled. Easy to disable per-restart.
